text:
If you don't have modern place value numeracy colliding with an ancient alphabetical numeracy, you can't do digital reduction, but you can do factorial reduction (terminating at the first non-composite number). 
For instance:
666 (37 x 3 x 3 x 2) -> 45 (5 x 3 x 3) -> 11
National leaders are strangely reluctant to whack each other as well.
... Hominids had to end up with 10 prehensile digits for eschatological reasons.
What is it about Diversity Exclusion and Inequality that they don't understand?
... If you never suspected there was anything especially strange about the number four before this, you might afterwards.

George Chapman:
"No pen can any thing eternal write, 
That is not steept in humour of the night."
-- What a guy.

Factorial Reduction: "While walking along in desert sand, you suddenly look down and see a tortoise crawling toward you ..."
Four: "Ha, turtles, easy ..."
If your concrete politics (i.e. effective policy suite) results inevitably in mass child rape, you might not actually be on the side of the angels.
